'''Yatsurugi Shrines''' (八剣神社, also written as 剱神社, 劔神社, or 劍神社) also read as Yatsurugi Shrines refer to {{ill|Shinto shrines|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. These shrines often enshrine eight swords as sacred objects or deities, including {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素戔嗚尊|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
